        "body": "### Prerequisites\n\n- [x] I have written a descriptive issue title\n- [x] I have searched existing issues to ensure the feature has not already been requested\n\n\n### 🚀 Feature Proposal\n\nThe Mongoose docs currently do not provide a way to quickly copy code examples.  \nFor users reading guides, tutorials, and API docs, this slows down the workflow and leads to manual text selection.\n\n### Problem\n- No built-in copy-to-clipboard feature.\n- Users must manually select and copy code snippets.\n- Inconsistent with modern documentation UX standards.\n\n### Proposed Enhancement\nAdd a small copy-to-clipboard button that:\n- Appears when hovering over a code block.\n- Uses a minimal SVG icon with clean styling.\n- Shows a checkmark briefly after copying.\n- Includes hover animations and smooth transitions.\n- Provides accessibility via `aria-label`.\n\n### Benefit\nGreatly improves the UX for all developers reading the documentation and aligns with common patterns in most major libraries.\n\n### Implementation\nThe feature is already implemented locally:\n- JS: Dynamically adds a copy button to each `<pre><code>` block.\n- CSS: Handles styling, positioning, animations, and success state.\n\nTested using `npm run docs:view` and works across all documentation pages.\n\nA pull request with the implementation will follow.",
